ACTRESS Zola Nombona honoured Orlando Pirates at the Durban July! The former Generations: The Legacy actress shook things up on Twitter when she showed up at the Durban July in a black dress, written 85, on Saturday, 2 June. The 30-year-old actress from Mthatha, Eastern Cape, said the dress was her way of celebrating Pirates’ anniversary. The team was founded by James Mpanza as Orlando Boys Club in 1985. The actress was praised by many of her followers, including Pirates fans. ALSO READ: Mzansi stars brought the honey to Durban July She wrote on Twitter that this was her first-ever Durban July experience held at the Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban, KZN. It’s my first #DurbanJuly experience and the best part is that I am celebrating the start of the @orlandopirates 85th Anniversary ?? with my @adidasZA fam #OnceAlways-Dress @Fundudzi pic.twitter.com/8GiiyEjkVU  Zola wrote: “It’s my first #DurbanJuly experience and the best part is that I’m celebrating the start of the @orlandopirates 85th anniversary with my @adidasZA fam.” Zola was dressed by local label, Fundudzi. “Don’t you get tired of eating up every single look?” said Kgware Paballo. “Trust Zola Nombona to dress up and show up. Queen of drip that one,” said Naledi Aphane. Shardie Brown said people needed to stop sleeping on Zola. “This lady never disappoints. Always understands the assignment. She ate this look and left no crumbs. Sickening,” she said. The hastag of the day was #durbanjuly2022.